---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About Us | CarbideSaws.com Industrial Services"
  description="Professional saw sharpening and blade repair since 1985. CNC precision grinding, custom manufacturing, and technical support for industrial cutting operations."
>
  <section class="gradient-hero text-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-6">About CarbideSaws.com</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100">
          Professional saw services since 1985. CNC precision grinding for industrial cutting operations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose-custom">
        <h2>Four Decades of Precision</h2>
        <p>
          Since 1985, CarbideSaws.com has served sawmills, metal fabrication facilities, and industrial 
          manufacturers with precision saw sharpening and custom blade manufacturing. Our investment in 
          CNC grinding technology and metallurgical expertise sets us apart from general machine shops.
        </p>

        <h3>Our Technology</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">CNC Grinding Centers</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Multi-axis machines with digital tooth profile scanning for precise geometry restoration.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Diamond & CBN Wheels</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Premium grinding media for carbide, cermet, and high-speed steel.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Flood Coolant Systems</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Temperature-controlled grinding prevents thermal damage to blade temper.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Precision Measurement</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Digital verification of all angles, tolerances, and surface finishes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Industries Served</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Sawmill Operations:</strong> Circular and band saw blades for dimensional lumber</li>
          <li><strong>Metal Fabrication:</strong> Cold saws, band saws for structural steel</li>
          <li><strong>Countertop Fabrication:</strong> Diamond and carbide for stone/composite</li>
          <li><strong>Pallet Manufacturing:</strong> High-volume resaw and trim applications</li>
          <li><strong>Furniture Production:</strong> Precision cutting for fine woodworking</li>
          <li><strong>Industrial Manufacturing:</strong> Custom solutions for specialized applications</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Our Commitment</h3>
        <p>
          We don't just sharpen blades—we diagnose cutting problems. Our application engineers provide 
          recommendations on blade selection, cutting parameters, and maintenance practices to maximize 
          your operational efficiency.
        </p>

        <h3>Quality Guarantee</h3>
        <p>
          Every blade we service undergoes rigorous quality control. If a repaired blade doesn't meet 
          specifications, we'll make it right. Our reputation depends on your satisfaction.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Work With Us</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
        Experience the difference precision engineering makes.
      </p>
      <a href="/carbidesaws-rebuild/contact" class="bg-secondary text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary transition">
        Get Started
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
